### ⬇️ Protected Routes (require Firebase ID Token)
# Before running, replace <YOUR_ID_TOKEN> with a real token:
# 1. Sign in on frontend
# 2. Run in browser console: await auth.currentUser.getIdToken()
# 3. Copy the token and paste it below

### Upsert User Profile (create/update)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/users/testuser123
Authorization: Bearer <YOUR_ID_TOKEN>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Miratun Nahar",
  "email": "miratun@example.com",
  "interests": ["AI", "Machine Learning", "Career Guidance"]
}

### Fetch User Profile
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/users/testuser123
